July is going to be a crazy month for the Beyhive. Queen of global entertainment, Beyoncé, just dropped a surprise visual album trailer. Her new visual album, Black Is King, is inspired by The Lion King and will premiere on 31 July. It comes a year after the release of The Lion King: The Gift, in which she voiced Nala. It is in partnership with Disney Plus, a subscription video-on-demand streaming service. Beyoncé is the writer, director and executive producer of the album. It features various artists: Childish Gambino, Kendrick Lamar, Pharrell, 070 Shake, Tierra Whack, Jay-Z, Blue Ivy Carter and Jessie Reyez. It also features African artists including Wizkid, Shatta Wale, Burna Boy, Mr Eazi, Tiwa Savage, Tekno, Yemi Alade, Busiswa and Salatiel.  